name: Torbole Holiday House - Appartamento con giardino
neighborhood_overview:
Torbole on Lake Garda is a fascination for sport fans

Torbole, situated on the Northern gulf of Lake Garda, between Monte Baldo on the Eastern side and the Sarche plain on the Northern side, is the most sought-after destination for windsurfing fans. It is a sailing and windsurfing centre of international relevance. Torbole on Lake Garda is also a starting point for mountain bike excursions, easy walks and treks. 
Torbole used to be a little fishing and boating village. The tiny harbour is the most picturesque corner of Torbole, with its Old Customs House and House Beust.
Torbole fascinated even Goethe, who described its winds as one of the wonders of nature and a breathtaking sight. The enthusiastic descriptions of Goethe prompted many young painters and poets to visit Torbole on Lake Garda as part of  their Grand Tours.

name: Apartment for 5-7 persons with 2 bathrooms
neighborhood_overview:
Pozza di Fassa is a nice alpine town located in the heart of Val di Fassa. It is an ideal location for those who love the mountains and would like to discover the Dolomites. The typical alpine style town offers various possibilities to spend a wonderful holiday in the Alps in the winter and in the summer for adults and children. Here you will find many craft shops, traditional Italian and South Tyrol restaurants, shops bars etc.

The village of Pera, where our residence with 8 apartments is located, is a fraction of Pozza and there is just a 10-minute walk between 2 villages. A supermarket, bakery, ATM bancomat is 300 meters from our house, pizzeria at 50 meters and restaurant-pizzeria 200 meters, ski/snowboard/bike rent 50 meters.

In the winter, the Val di Fassa is a genuine paradise for skiers with more than 200 km of slopes and countless connections with the surrounding ski resorts. But this beautiful Dolomite valley is not only ideal for downhill ski fanatics.

name: Blue Nest Apartment - WiFi - Lake Garda
neighborhood_overview:
Torbole is a small town situated in the northeastern corner of Lake Garda.
It is a strategic point for people who love both relaxing and active holidays.
This place is certainly a must for sailing and windsurfing lovers but, in the last ten years, it  became also a very popular destination for biking and trekking activities.
The mountains that rise from the city (Monte Altissimo and Monte Brione) are perfect for a spectacular walk and for unique bike trails (Dh, enduro and all-mountain).
The town is characterized by long and quiet beaches where you can spend the whole day under the sun, tasting good food and enjoying the amazing view.
It also offers every kind of commercial activities (shops, surf and sailing centers, bike rentals) and every kind of amenities you could need.
Don't miss the old town with it's small harbour and the picturesque cottage of Dazio.

name: Mansarda Trentino-Campiglio
neighborhood_overview:
Ossana is situated at the beginning of the Val di Peio valley, at the foot of the Presanella group. In the past it served as main religious center of the whole valley and assumed power thanks to the castle of S. Michele. Besides, the castle Ossana features also other remarkable historical and cultural buildings, as for example several churches which are scattered around its various hamlets. Its territory allows to practice numerous sport activities, both in summer and in winter.
Ossana, awarded the "Most beautiful sky in Italy" certification, is a small settlement which lies just in the middle of the northern part of Val di Sole and offers several interesting amenities, as for example its old castle. The Castle of San Michele is dated back to the Lombards and was owned by several noble families. This stronghold is located in an unusual position, in fact it lies on a rock and is hardly accessible from three sides. Its quadrangular tower is a landmark for the whole Val di Sole valle

name: Cesa Rois - Apartment 1
neighborhood_overview: Canazei is considered the skiing capital of the Val di Fassa and is now known throughout the international skiing. Those who take the comfortable automatic cable car from the town center is located within minutes projected into the largest and most spectacular skiing circuit in the world: the Sella Ronda. On the wide, sunny valley of the Belvedere, thanks to the many facilities it is possible not only on the ski area itself, but also to enter the famous circuit of the Dolomiti Superski. The choices are many, ranging from easy slopes, the average, up to one marked in black suits skiers more daring. In summer Canazei offers many ideas for memorable excursions. Some names of the Dolomite peaks, such as Pordoi, Sella and Marmolada evoke from the hikes and climbs that have made history in the world of the mountain. Between summer and winter the enthusiast is facing the embarrassment of choice. In Canazei Boredom it is not even at night!

name: Your alpine home with panoramic view
neighborhood_overview:
Pozza di Fassa is a nice alpine town located in the heart of Val di Fassa. It is an ideal location for those who love the mountains and would like to discover the Dolomites. The typical alpine style town offers various possibilities to spend a wonderful holiday in the Alps in the winter and in the summer for adults and children. Here you will find many craft shops, traditional Italian and South Tyrol restaurants, shops bars etc.

The village of Pera, where our residence with 8 apartments is located, is a fraction of Pozza and there is just a 10-minute walk between 2 villages. A supermarket, bakery, ATM bancomat is 300 meters from our house, pizzeria at 50 meters and restaurant-pizzeria 200 meters, ski/snowboard/bike rent 50 meters.

In the winter, the Val di Fassa is a genuine paradise for skiers with more than 200 km of slopes and countless connections with the surrounding ski resorts. But this beautiful Dolomite valley is not only ideal for downhill ski fanatics.

name: Tuckett lodge - A flat for families and friends
neighborhood_overview:
Tuckett Lodge is located in Campo Carlo Magno and is about 3km from the center of Madonna di Campiglio.
In winter the ski bus stop is 50 meters from the apartment and offers a direct connection to the ski slopes and the village center.
For lovers of Nordic skiing and snowshoeing the center for Nordic skiing is located opposite the entrance of the apartment building.

In summer the location is ideal to take a walk in the woods of the Natural ParK Adamello - Brenta and reach the alpine lakes, alpine pastures, pastures and high mountain trails inside the Dolomites of Brenta.

For lovers of golf, the Golf Club Campo Carlo Magno, with its 9-hole course designed by Henry Cotton in 1920, is a 2-minute drive.

Service in the area - 500 meters: supermarket, tobacco, newspapers, restaurants and bars, ski schools, sporting equipment rental, ATM

name: Apt. Moena - Rododentro - San Pellegrino (mt 1900)
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is located at the San Pellegrino pass (1918m), in the south from the Marmolada mountain range, in the heart of the Dolomites.
In summer the apartment is surrounded by acres of meadows, woods and lakes, set on one of the sunniest Dolomite plateaus, next to the mythical "Alta Via" road and cycle and mountain bike trails.
Hut-to-hut hikes suitable for all ages. Relaxing moments on the shores of mountain lakes, demanding hikes along the Bepi Zac via ferrata.
In winter the superb slopes with state-of-the-art lift facilities are only few metres from the residence. With one single ski pass you can enjoy more than 100 km of slopes, of which 90 km with artificial snow from November to May. 12 chair lifts (of which 2 double, 3 triple, 7 quadruple), 1 cable railway and 14 t-bar lifts.
Snow fun doesn¬¥t stop here: 20 km of cross-country trails, ski schools, sports shops with ski equipment rental.

name: Cosy studio near slopes, modem provided bring SIM
neighborhood_overview:
Val di Fassa is full of charming small towns and full of curiosity. The food is delicious and the nature charming. The surroundings of the residence Solaria are full of ski slopes for winter (in Campitello is easy access to the Sellaronda- tour of the 4 passes) and in summer you can access the most beautiful walks, from the most simple to the experts. In Canazei you can spend a beautiful day of shopping or relaxing in the beautiful aquatic center Dolandes
GETTING AROUND
Mazzin is located right along the main road that connects the Val di Fassa and Val di Fiemme and the residence Solaria is located a few minutes walk from the main local bus-stop, number 101, which connects the valley with Trento. To reach the valley from abroad you can fly to many destinations in the surroundungs and then connect easily to Trento

name: Central Canazei Ski APT "C" - Perfect Location
neighborhood_overview:
This apartment is located in the lovely ski-town of Canazei, Italy. It is only a 10 minute walk down the hill to the ski lift "Funivia Belvedere", and it is located at the edge of the ski run.

In Canazei there is a big and brand new indoor heated pool with a spa and plenty of other activities and attractions, such as a super market, cinema, library, restaurants, pizzerias, shops, boutiques, bowling, parks, Ping-Pong, games for children and a weekend market (on Saturdays).
Canazei is the starting point for countless excursions suitable for children and experts. There is a beautiful, recently renewed, mountain bike-riding trek of 40 km long which runs throughout the entire valley and up to Molina di Fiemme. The arrival stations of the cable cars, Belvedere and the Ciampac, at high altitude, is also the starting point for extreme sports such as hiking, climbing, free riding and downhill biking.

In addition the famous kosher ‚ÄúMyHotel‚Äù is just 1 KM outside of Cana

name: Lisi's place
neighborhood_overview:
The living room (perfect as play room) faces the village square: Lisignago has maintained its ancient origins. This is an urban center of ancient origins, located on the banks of the Avisio stream, at the foot of the mountains. In this small village you can spend a very active holiday in the nature or a relaxing holiday with family and friends.

The best season to come here is summer, when nature is at its best: forests and meadows, contrasting with the many vineyard covered terracing. The best way to become familiar with this area is to walk, and here surely there is no lack of trails: from those running on the valley floors, suitable also for children, to high altitude trails. There are also many natural attractions, like the Pyramids of Segonzano. If you love horseback riding you have at your disposal many trails winding through charming landscapes.

Percorrendo la strada verso Piazza Duomo incontrerete la sede della Societ√† Filarmonica di Trento (1795), proprio poco prima di giungere dinanzi all‚Äôingresso principale della Cattedrale di San Vigilio (1212).

Svoltando a destra, una breve passeggiata attraverso il centro storico vi consentir√† di giungere in Piazza Fiera, sede dei noti mercatini di Natale.

name: Lake view apartment with huge terrace
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is located high above the Caldonazzo lake, in a perfect position to reach quite a few highlights of the region. The beautiful lake itself is only minutes away. You can reach the state capital, Trento, with its historical city center and all the shops and services you might need in about half an hour with the car, which is the same time you need to reach Folgaria and its ski slopes (both downhill and cross-country). The neighbouring towns of Levico and Roncegno are famous for their thermal baths. The Garda Lake, the slopes in Cavalese and the city of Bolzano are all reachable within an hour, as are many of Trentino's picturesque valleys and towns and all the activities they offer (skiing, biking, hiking,...).

name: Casa del Prenner - Meditation & Relax
neighborhood_overview:
Ziano lies along the Avisio stream, in front of the majestic Catena del Lagorai, right at the point where the valley makes a wide curve. The wide green expanses, mostly flat, and reach the edges of the inhabited center.
With its extensive network of hiking trails in the Dolomitic Group of the Latemar and the Lagorai Chain, Ziano di Fiemme is a summer and winter resort.
The village in summer overlooks the Dolomites cycle path and in winter on the legendary cross-country ski run of the Marcialonga. It is also close to the ski lifts of the Ski Center Latemar and Alpe Cermis.

name: Meoni - Arnica -  022039-AT-903901
neighborhood_overview:
Penia is a fraction of the municipality of Canazei, in Val di Fassa, on the course of the Avisio stream.
Located at a  height of 1555 m above sea level, the small town of Penia, with a parish church, is directly connected to the hamlet of Alba di Canazei and, consequently, to its ski resorts. This means that the village is a well-known holiday resort both in winter and in the summer, thanks to the presence of numerous trails that start from the center to reach the Marmolada, Monzoni and Sella group.
Penia is an official stopover place along the famous Via Alpina, a path that runs from east to west across the mountain range of the Alps. The condominium is located about 1000 meters from the Ciampac and Col de Rossi cable cars. The ski bus stop is 400 meters away and the center of Alba di Canazei is about 1100 meters, with all the services of pizzerias and shops with winter and summer equipment rental.

name: Windsurfer's Suite - Garda Lake View
neighborhood_overview:
Torbole, situated on the Northern gulf of Lake Garda, between Monte Baldo on the Eastern side and the Sarche plain on the Northern side, is the most sought-after destination for windsurfing fans. It is a sailing and windsurfing centre of international relevance. Torbole on Lake Garda is also a starting point for mountain bike excursions, easy walks and treks. Torbole used to be a little fishing and boating village. The tiny harbour is the most picturesque corner of Torbole, with its Old Customs House and House Beust. Torbole fascinated even Goethe, who described its winds as one of the wonders of nature and a breathtaking sight. The enthusiastic descriptions of Goethe prompted many young painters and poets to visit Torbole on Lake Garda as part of  their Grand Tours.

name: RIVA DEL GARDA flat with terrace
neighborhood_overview:
It is located in a unique position and just a few steps from Lake Garda, the beach and the lakeside cycle path leading to the centre or to Torbole sul Garda. The characteristic historical centre is 10 minutes walking distance, while the main services (supermarket, bank, pharmacy...) are on the other side of the street.
Riva del Garda is a characteristic town that directly overlooks the shores of Lake Garda. Enclosed in its picturesque old town, it boasts a beautiful cycle/pedestrian path that runs along the entire lake, a glass lift that leads to the walls of the ancient Bastion of Riva del Garda from which you can enjoy a breathtaking view. There are many routes for hikers and trekking lovers, to do also by mountain bike

name: Chalet Schwarzhorn - Enjoy the Dolomites
neighborhood_overview:
Varena lies in an excellent position, nestled at the foot of the mount Corno Nero. This village is one of the most ancient centres of Trentino. Walking in Varena you can stare at typical monolithic porphyry fountains. According to the tradition, from the fountains of Varena sprang the best drinkable water of the valley. The church of Varena - consecrated in the Thirteenth century - is dedicated to the saints Pietro and Paolo and the internal Gothic and medieval decorations are worth a visit ‚Äì the masterpieces were made by Longo and the paintings by Unterperger.
Around the village there are numerous flat and panoramic walks.
At Christmas time, Varena shows a very famous and attractive crib, called ‚ÄúSulla via di Betlemme", ‚ÄúOn the road to Betlemme‚Äù, with hundreds of Arabian-style characters and animals that reproduce the story of Nativity.

what to see and do in the surroundings

Things to do and see in Riva del Garda
Riva del Garda is the second largest city on the lake and the true and undisputed capital of adventure!

What to see in Riva del Garda Center,
what to do if you love adventure and sport,
what to see and do in the surroundings
and also some places to go to satisfy your taste buds!

Riva del Garda is a pretty town on the northern coast of Lake Garda surrounded by steep cliffs and high mountains
particularly suggestive if you arrive by boat.
Riva has a small historic center with picturesque streets and numerous shops and restaurants.

So even in Riva itself there are enough attractions to spend a few days even if the city is above all an excellent base both for experiencing the lake and for exploring the mountains.

Riva del Garda has a more "urban" atmosphere than the nearby small villages and in short, for how many days you decide to stay, you won't have time to get bored:

name: A short walk from the center and the lake
neighborhood_overview:
Things to do and see in Riva del Garda
Riva del Garda is the second largest city on the lake and the true and undisputed capital of adventure!

What to see in Riva del Garda Center,
what to do if you love adventure and sport,
what to see and do in the surroundings
and also some places to go to satisfy your taste buds!

Riva del Garda is a pretty town on the northern coast of Lake Garda surrounded by steep cliffs and high mountains
particularly suggestive if you arrive by boat.
Riva has a small historic center with picturesque streets and numerous shops and restaurants.

So even in Riva itself there are enough attractions to spend a few days even if the city is above all an excellent base both for experiencing the lake and for exploring the mountains.

Riva del Garda has a more "urban" atmosphere than the nearby small villages and in short, for how many days you decide to stay, you won't have time to get bored:

name: Biacesa di Ledro - Garda Studio "Mount 'N Lake"
neighborhood_overview:
Posizione ottima per sport: passeggiate, trekking e ferrate con partenza direttamente da Biacesa:
il sentiero al Lago di Ledro (foot/bike, 6 km), la famosa panoramica "Strada del Ponale" per Riva del Garda (foot & bike, 9km) !!chiusa dal 28.09. a marzo '21 per manutenzione!!, Cima Capi, Rocchetta e le gallerie della 1¬∞ guerra.
Biacesa (460 m s.l.m.) e' un paesino montano di 200 abitanti che si trova sulla strada che porta da Riva del Garda (70 m.l.m.) in Valle di Ledro e il suo lago eponimo (655 m.l.m.).
Qui potete trovare una popolare osteria tipica, un climber-bar, una troticoltura, un campo sportivo libero e tante fontane con dell'ottima acqua di montagna.
Il Lago di Ledro offre sentieri, acque cristalline, spiagge, noleggio pedalo', catamarani, canoe, SUP,  bici e e-bike, ristoranti con specialita' trentine e inoltre un interessante "Museo delle Palaffitte". Da visitare anche il monumento Garibaldi a Bezzecca e il biotopo Lago d'Ampola.
La Valle di Ledro

name: Chalet De L'Or - Bellamonte Alpe Lusia Dolomites
neighborhood_overview:
Bellamonte, a fraction of Predazzo, is commonly considered one of the most evocative places in the Val di Fiemme as well as in the Trentino, thanks to its fortunate position, with one of the most beautiful views of the Pale di San Martino group and the vast prairies that surround the characteristic huts in fir logs and stones.
In a few minutes you can reach the ski lifts of Passo Rolle, Castelir Alpe Lusia, the Ski Center Latemar or those of San Martino Tognola.
In a few minutes by car you can reach the beautiful Paneveggio Natural Park where there is a visitor area that offers beautiful guided tours. Continuing, it is possible to reach the Rolle pass and the Val Venegia car parks from where the excursions in the Pale di San Martino group start.
The center of Predazzo is about 15 minutes from the apartment.

name: Al Maset
neighborhood_overview:
Pergine Valsugana is a big village of about 20,000 population. Beside the castle, it is nice to have a walk in the village center where, on saturday morning, you can find a market. Just a few kilometres away there's the Caldonazzo lake, with beaches, water sports and a beautiful cycling road that goes until Bassano del Grappa. A short distance away there's the wild Levico Lake and Levico Terme, always hosting some interesting event.
You can reach Trento by car, in about 10/15 minutes, or you can take the train that runs between Trento and Venice.
Pergine is at the door of the Mocheni Valley and the Lagorai range: trekking, walks, mountain bike, horse riding...there's something for everyone!

name: Antica Contrada Apartment
neighborhood_overview:

Near the Palacongressi lies Fraglia Vela Riva where sailing courses are offered for children and adults. Also, just 2 minutes from the apartment you will find the port with boat mooring and ferry to reach many special and famous towns of Lake Garda such as Torbole, Limone, Malcesine, Garda, Peschiera, Desenzano and many others.

The strategically located position of Riva del Garda allows one to enjoy many sports and activities such as sailing windsurfing, mountain and nature walks as well as cycling on one of the many mountain bike trails.  The city of Trento is only 45kms away and hosts the new Muse Museum. In the winter the ski areas of San Valentino, Bondone , Folgaria and Madonna di Campiglio are only 30-45 mins drive away. neighborhood_overview:
Its Mediterranean climate, wide sunny beaches and beautiful panorama are the right ingredients for an unforgettable holiday on Lake Garda ‚Äì or more than one if you wish!
Riva del Garda is the main centre of Northern Lake Garda. It is the ideal location for an eventful holiday. Sport is the main motivation for the holiday: sailing and windsurfing in the first instance, but also hiking, cycling, mountain biking, tennis, canoeing. The mild climate favours a typically Mediterranean vegetation with lemon trees, olive trees, laurels and palm trees: a true Mediterranean island at the foot of the Dolomites. The centre of Riva del Garda will fascinate you with its works of art and architecture, witnessing to ancient history and a past rich in art and culture.

name: Casa Masetto, large apartment with balconies
neighborhood_overview: Casa Masetto is located in a fantastic position, in a rather quiet residential area to enjoy moments of leisure and relaxation. Riva del Garda is considered by many to be the pearl of Lake Garda, it is a place enclosed in a territory of strong contrasts, with Mediterranean vegetation that grows vigorously at the foot of rocky walls around which a cobalt blue lake is set. Here the holiday embraces a thousand experiences, sport first of all: sailing and windsurfing, but also trekking, cycling, mountain biking, climbing, tennis and rowing. With a quiet walk towards the center you can access the many attractions such as: the Rocca, the Apponale Tower, the Palazzo Pretorio, the Church of the Inviolata and the church of Santa Maria Assunta, the hydroelectric plant and the Ponale path.

neighborhood_overview:
The  cable car from the Passo della Mendola takes you directly from the Passo della Mendola to Caldaro on foot or by bike. From there you can start a great tour through the surrounding communities such as Caldaro, Appiano and Termeno. Your tour will take you through the legendary area of many castles and manors with its vineyards and apple orchards.
From the Passo della Mendola you can easily reach the unique viewpoint of Penegal on foot or by car. Enjoy the enchanting view of Bolzano and far into the lowlands while sipping a glass of wine.
For hikers with children there are many beautiful short and longer tours to our alpine huts Genzianells, Halbwegh√ºtte, Malga Romeno.
On the Trentino side, in the nearby village of Ruffr√® with its 407 inhabitants, there is a riding stable for horse lovers where children and adults are welcome and can book rides and riding lessons.

name: Ciasa Buro - Gimel
neighborhood_overview:
Moena is the gateway of Val di Fassa, a valley in the heart of the Northeastern Alps in the region of Trentino.

Located at an altitude of 1.184 m, Moena is at the foot of the majestic Dolomites, a UNESCO World Heritage Site since 2009.

It is an elegant and traditional village imbued with a fairy tale atmosphere and nested in steep coral peaks.
In the centre, small bridges cross the sparkling river Avisio and small gravel trails follow its stream. In winter, when nature is in hibernating mode and snowy crystals fall off the sky, the town shows all its beauty with Christmas lights, ice sculptures, cozy restaurants and shops. In summer, the warm weather and fresh alpine breeze invite you to discover the narrow alleys and flowery balconies. When fewer people walk through its roads and squares, Moena calmly reveals its hidden creations: while flora and fauna reemerge in spring, autumn gets painting showing its outstanding colors.

name: Casa Betulla - Attic in ARCO with Castel View
neighborhood_overview:
Despite the proximity to the historic center of Arco, the ancient district of San Martino remains a quiet and residential area, where mass tourism has not yet arrived.
You will find a unique and characteristic environment, with stone houses and the unfailing arched wooden doors, narrow streets, the typical fountain for the washerwomen in the central square where children are still allowed to play and the millenary church of San Martino which rises between the houses and the olive grove (olivaia).
Families have lived here for generations and have handed down ancient traditions such as the cultivation of olive trees and vineyards.
So...keep the secret! ;-)

name: Your home in the center of Val di Fassa
neighborhood_overview:
Pozza di Fassa is a nice alpine town located in the heart of Val di Fassa. It is an ideal location for those who love the mountains and would like to discover the Dolomites. The typical alpine style town offers various possibilities to spend a wonderful holiday in the Alps in the winter and in the summer for adults and children. Here you will find many craft shops, traditional Italian and South Tyrol restaurants, shops bars etc.

The village of Pera, where our residence with 8 apartments is located, is a fraction of Pozza and there is just a 10-minute walk between 2 villages. A supermarket, bakery, ATM bancomat is 300 meters from our house, pizzeria at 50 meters and restaurant-pizzeria 200 meters, ski/snowboard/bike rent 50 meters.

In the winter, the Val di Fassa is a genuine paradise for skiers with more than 200 km of slopes and countless connections with the surrounding ski resorts. But this beautiful Dolomite valley is not only ideal for downhill ski fanatics.

neighborhood_overview:
A Segonzano trovi un ambiente ricco di  percorsi in stradine di campagna con poco o per nulla trafficate, borghi e paesini da scoprire. Inoltre ci sono percorsi nel bosco adatti alla bicicletta, per gli amanti della bici  attraverso  Albergo Piramidi  c'√® la possibilit√† di noleggio bike. (n limitato)
Per chi ama il trekking i percorsi a piedi non mancano, chi desidera fare  brevi  passeggiate o itinerari giornalieri ricever√†  informazioni all'arrivo.
Il Paese di Segonzano si trovo in  Valle di Cembra, tappa ideale  per  raggiungere in poco tempo la Valle di  Fiemme e Fassa, localit√† conosciute oltre che per i panorami Dolomitici,  per l'offerta di molti impianti sciistici.
A circa mezz'ora di macchina dal paese di Segonzano si raggiunge la  citt√† di Trento. Molti sono i punti di interesse,  alcune tappe possibili.
